f:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates funding rates every hour based on the premium/discount between perpetual and mark prices, using a dampening factor to reduce extreme rates. The exchange's on-chain order book ensures transparent price discovery while maintaining CEX-grade execution speeds with sub-second finality. Funding payments occur automatically in USDC, with rates typically ranging from -2% to +2% annually for PEPE during normal market conditions."}]
10:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","PEPE","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PEPE's extreme volatility and retail-driven trading patterns create frequent funding rate imbalances on Hyperliquid, especially during trending market phases. The combination of high trading volume and meme token speculation leads to substantial premium/discount cycles that arbitrageurs can exploit. Hyperliquid's 1-hour funding frequency allows for more responsive positioning compared to 8-hour intervals on traditional exchanges."}]]}]
11:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PEPE funding rates on Hyperliquid exhibit pronounced cyclical behavior, often spiking above +1% hourly during bullish meme coin rallies and turning deeply negative during corrections. Weekend periods typically show elevated rates due to reduced arbitrage activity and increased retail speculation. The token's correlation with broader meme coin sentiment creates predictable rate patterns around major social media events and influencer mentions. Historical data shows funding rates exceeding ±0.5% hourly occur approximately 15-20% of the time for PEPE on Hyperliquid."}]]}]
12:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid's isolated USDC ecosystem creates arbitrage opportunities when PEPE funding rates diverge from other major exchanges like Binance or Bybit. The 1-hour funding interval enables traders to capture short-term rate spikes that would be averaged out over 8-hour periods elsewhere. Cross-DEX arbitrage strategies can exploit Hyperliquid's premium/discount cycles by hedging positions on CEXs with different funding schedules. The platform's no-KYC structure and on-chain transparency make it attractive for automated arbitrage strategies targeting PEPE rate inefficiencies."}]]}]
13:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"PEPE's extreme volatility can cause significant mark-to-market losses that exceed funding rate profits, particularly during flash crashes or pump events. Hyperliquid's single L1 ecosystem presents concentration risk, as network congestion or technical issues could prevent timely position adjustments. The relatively new exchange lacks the operational track record of established platforms, introducing counterparty and smart contract risks for large positions. Meme token funding arbitrage requires careful position sizing due to PEPE's tendency for gap movements that can trigger liquidations despite positive funding flows."}]]}]
14:["$","$L16",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does PEPE funding reset on Hyperliquid compared to other exchanges?","answer":"Hyperliquid resets PEPE funding rates every hour, compared to 8-hour intervals on most CEXs like Binance and OKX. This higher frequency allows traders to capture short-term funding rate spikes and reduces the averaging effect seen on traditional exchanges."},{"question":"What's the maximum funding rate for PEPE on Hyperliquid?","answer":"While Hyperliquid doesn't impose hard caps, PEPE funding rates are dampened through their calculation mechanism to prevent extreme rates. Historical maximums have reached approximately ±2% hourly during exceptional market events, though typical ranges stay within ±0.5% hourly."},{"question":"Can I use leverage for PEPE funding arbitrage on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Yes, Hyperliquid offers up to 50x leverage on PEPE perpetuals, but funding arbitrage strategies typically use lower leverage (5-10x) to avoid liquidation during the token's volatile price swings. Higher leverage amplifies both funding profits and mark-to-market risks."},{"question":"How does Hyperliquid's on-chain structure affect PEPE funding calculations?","answer":"The fully on-chain order book provides transparent price discovery for PEPE mark price calculations, reducing manipulation risks compared to oracle-dependent systems. However, the L1's block times and potential congestion can occasionally affect the precision of funding rate updates during extreme volatility."}]}]
